<<info_map>>
🗺 Map

Coordinates are written as two numbers, where 1x1 is the bottom-left corner of the map.

Legend:
{0}

To move to another location:
🔼 /up /north
◀️ /left /west
▶️ /right /east
🔽 /down /south

You can add a number to specify a more distant target:
For example, /up_3 - movement 3 cells up

There's also a command to move to a selected location. For example, to move to location 3x4, write /go_3_4
Travel takes a lot of time and consumes energy, so you can use caravan services (see /caravan for details)
<</info_map>>